cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY 

This paper is about reinforcement learning for robots, specifically exploring distributed and asynchronous policy learning. The focus is on real-world manipulation tasks, which suggests robotics (cs.RO) as the most likely category. The use of guided policy search and the emphasis on learning complex and general skills suggests machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as likely categories. The vision-based door opening task suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as a possible category. Finally, the use of multiple robots and the emphasis on coordination and control suggest systems and control (cs.SY) as a possible category.
